        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix one-shot Codex app-server teardown",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Close the Codex app-server shared client after one-shot OpenClaw agent runs finish.\n- Thread cleanup metadata through gateway/CLI agent paths so CLI sessions do not leave app-server or Agent Hub proxy children behind.\n- Add regression coverage for cleanup, gateway propagation, and session resume behavior.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** One-shot Codex/OpenClaw agent runs could leave shared app-server and Agent Hub proxy children alive after the run ended, which made Jarvis/fleet sessions accumulate stale processes and degraded multi-session reliability.\n- **Real environment tested:** Live managed OpenClaw runtime on `openclaw-vm01`, host runtime `OpenClaw 2026.6.2 (a23b0c7)`, managed plugin `@openclaw/codex 2026.6.2`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran a Jarvis managed-plugin smoke session through the real OpenClaw gateway using session `agent:jarvis:teardown-source-aligned-smoke-20260609161031`; then checked runtime cleanup logs and waited 25 seconds before checking for lingering `codex app-server` or `agent-hub-proxy.ts` children.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from the live smoke showed `embedded fallback: false`, assistant reply `gateway path ok`, cleanup log `activeLeases=0 closed=true matchedSharedClient=true`, and the 25s post-run process check found no Codex app-server or Agent Hub proxy children except the grep process.\n- **Observed result after fix:** The live run completed on the gateway path and cleaned up the shared managed-plugin client without leaving stale child processes behind.\n- **What was not tested:** Full production merge/release rollout was not tested in this PR; validation was limited to local CI-equivalent gates plus the live managed-plugin smoke on `openclaw-vm01`.\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `pnpm tsgo:prod`\n- `pnpm lint --threads=8`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.process.config.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `pnpm run lint:tmp:no-raw-channel-fetch`\n- `pnpm protocol:gen && pnpm protocol:gen:swift` with generated Swift protocol artifact included\n- Focused teardown/gateway tests and package/tarball validation were run before the live deployment smoke.",
